text: Nothofagus womersleyi is a species of plant in the Nothofagaceae (Southern beeches) family. It is endemic to West Papua (Indonesia). It was proposed to be renamed Trisyngyne womersleyi in 2013. It is an Endangered species threatened by habitat loss. ==References== Category:Nothofagaceae Category:Endemic flora of Western New Guinea Category:Endangered plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
